 Parallelizable |\n40: | `[B]` | Blocked |\n41: \n42: **Task Format**: `T### [P?] Description (file path)`\n43: <!-- /ANCHOR:notation -->\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: <!-- ANCHOR:phase-1 -->\n48: ## Phase 1: Setup\n49: \n50: - [x] T001 Capture live-DB fixture (edges at measured scale, degree distribution). Evidence: new vitest fixture uses 10,240 causal edges, max degree 20, seeds 5, hops 2.\n51: - [x] T002 Equivalence harness: record current CTE outputs as snapshots. Evidence: `causal-traversal-bfs-equivalence.vitest.ts` compares current CTE output to BFS output exactly.\n52: - [x] T003 [P] Traversal helper: hop-capped weighted walk mode. Evidence: `collectCausalWeightedNeighbors` in `lib/graph/bfs-traversal.ts`.\n53: <!-- /ANCHOR:phase-1 -->\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: <!-- ANCHOR:phase-2 -->\n58: ## Phase 2: Implementation\n59: \n60: - [x] T004 [P] Traversal helper: directed unbounded reachability mode. Evidence: `collectDependencyReachability` in `lib/graph/bfs-traversal.ts`.\n61: - [x] T005 getNeighborBoosts cutover behind engine flag. Evidence: equivalence suite passed, then `getNeighborBoosts` now calls the shared helper with CTE removed from source.\n62: - [x] T006 memo.ts collectDependents + wouldCreateCycle cutover with zero-row fast path. Evidence: new test spies `prepare` after store construction and confirms zero SELECTs for first insert into an empty edge table.\n63: <!-- /ANCHOR:phase-2 -->\n64: \n65: ---\n66: \n67: <!-- ANCHOR:phase-3 -->\n68: ## Phase 3: Verification\n69: \n70: - [x] T007 Equivalence suite green across fixtures. Evidence: `npx vitest run tests/causal-traversal-bfs-equivalence.vitest.ts --reporter verbose` passed 4/4 tests.\n71: - [x] T008 Latency benchmark vs CTE recorded. Evidence: fixture_edges=10240, max_degree=20, seeds=5, hops=2, CTE=1.429ms, BFS=1.117ms.\n72: - [x] T009 Remove flag; delete CTE paths. Evidence: source grep for `WITH RECURSIVE` in `mcp_server/lib` returned no matches.\n73: <!-- /ANCHOR:phase-3 -->\n74: \n75: ---\n76: